## Root Cause Analysis

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The low scores are NOT necessarily a sign of a broken parser — rather they reveal a **dataset mismatch**. Here's what's happening:

### 1. These Resumes Are Anonymized/Templated
The `INFORMATION-TECHNOLOGY` dataset appears to be from a resume repository (likely LiveCareer or similar) where:
- **Names, emails, and phones are redacted** or use non-standard formatting
- Text starts with job titles like `"INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY TECHNICIAN I"` rather than personal names
- Contact info uses formats like `Company Name ï¼​ City , State` with Unicode artifacts

### 2. Experience Date Pattern Mismatch
The parser's `YEAR_RANGE_PATTERN` looks for: `2020-2022` or `2020 to Present`  
But these resumes use: `Aug 2007 to Current` — the regex requires a dash/en-dash between years, but the resumes use **month + year + "to" + year/word** format.

### 3. spaCy NER Failing on Non-Standard Text
The entity extractor processes the first 1000 characters looking for `PERSON` entities, but these resumes:
- Start with job descriptions, not names
- Have garbled Unicode characters (`ï¼​`) that confuse the NER model
- Don't have standard "Name: John Doe" formatting

---

## What's Actually Working Well

| Component | Assessment |
|-----------|-----------|
| **PDF Text Extraction** | ✅ 100% success — all 120 PDFs extracted cleanly |
| **Skills Extraction** | ✅ 100% extraction rate, avg 6.4 skills/resume |
| **FAISS Semantic Matching** | ✅ Working correctly for skill variations |
| **Email Regex** (when present) | ✅ 100% format accuracy |
| **Phone Regex** (when present) | ✅ 86.7% format accuracy |

---

## Recommendations to Fix

### Priority 1: Fix Experience Date Pattern (Quick Win)
Update `YEAR_RANGE_PATTERN` in [config.py](file:///c:/Users/karti/computer_science/praktiki/PythonProject/resume_parser/config.py#L36-L39) to handle:
- `Aug 2007 to Current`
- `January 2015 to December 2020`
- `Mar 2019 - Present`

### Priority 2: Improve Name Extraction
Enhance [entity_extractor.py](file:///c:/Users/karti/computer_science/praktiki/PythonProject/resume_parser/entity_extractor.py#L35-L76):
- Add fallback: extract name from first few lines using heuristics
- Clean Unicode artifacts before NER processing
- Try larger text window (not just first 1000 chars)

### Priority 3: Test with Real Resumes
The `INFORMATION-TECHNOLOGY` dataset may not represent your production use case. Consider:
- Testing with actual user-submitted resumes (with consent)
- Creating a hand-labeled ground truth set for 10-20 resumes

